          "role": "user",
          "content": "Review my resume"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Excellent! I'm ready to provide a thorough and actionable review of your resume.\n\nTo get started, please paste the full content of your resume here. Once I have it, I'll analyze it for:\n\n1.  **ATS Optimization:** Ensuring it can pass Applicant Tracking Systems and be easily parsed.\n2.  **Impact and Achievements:** Checking that your accomplishments are quantified and impactful, rather than just listing duties.\n3.  **Clarity and Conciseness:** Making sure it's easy to read and understand, highlighting your most relevant skills and experiences.\n4.  **Keywords:** Identifying industry-specific keywords that will help your resume get noticed.\n5.  **Formatting and Readability:** Providing suggestions for layout, design, and overall presentation.\n6.  **Targeting:** How well it aligns with the types of roles you're pursuing.\n\nI look forward to helping you refine it!"
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Find gaps in my skills"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Absolutely! Pinpointing skill gaps is a crucial step in career development, ensuring you're always growing towards your professional goals.\n\nTo provide you with a *personalized* and *actionable* skill gap analysis, I need a little more information from you. Please tell me:\n\n1.  **Your Current Role/Experience:** A summary of your current professional background, including your industry, typical responsibilities, and key technologies/tools you currently use. (Even better, if you can paste your resume, that would be ideal!)\n2.  **Your Target Role/Industry:** What kind of role are you aspiring to next? What industry or specific companies are you interested in? This helps me understand the *destination* you're aiming for.\n3.  **Specific Areas of Interest:** Are there any particular technologies, methodologies, or domains you're keen to learn or improve in?\n\nOnce I have this context, I can analyze:\n*   **Required vs. Existing Skills:** Compare the skills demanded by your target roles against what you currently possess.\n*   **Industry Trends:** Highlight emerging skills that are becoming essential in your desired field.\n*   **Strategic Gaps:** Identify critical skills that, if acquired, would significantly boost your competitiveness and career trajectory.\n\nI'm ready when you are!"
        }
